# cluster.env.example — copy to `cluster.env` and edit for your two nodes.
#
#   cp cluster.env.example cluster.env && $EDITOR cluster.env
#
# `cluster.env` is git-ignored (it holds your hostnames) and is the single source
# of truth: every script sources it, and `render-env.sh` bakes these into the
# node-local `.env.dspark` that docker compose reads. Override any value per-run
# via the environment.

# =============================================================================
# 1. Node identity  — the ONLY block you must edit.
# =============================================================================
# Hostnames/aliases your control host can `ssh` to. mDNS (*.local) names or SSH
# aliases are ideal — avoid DHCP LAN IPs, which drift. HEAD is rank 0 (runs the
# OpenAI API + the head systemd unit); WORKER is rank 1 (headless).
HEAD_HOST=head.example.local
WORKER_HOST=worker.example.local

# Shared, unprivileged Linux user created on both nodes by 00-node-prep.sh.
# It is added to the `docker` group only — never to sudo. Keep it identical on
# both nodes (vLLM's multi-node launch assumes matching users/paths).
CLUSTER_USER=nvidia

# Where the kit is rsynced + run on each node, and where weights are cached.
# If you change CLUSTER_USER, update these homedirs to match.
KIT_DIR=/home/nvidia/dgx-cluster
HF_CACHE=/home/nvidia/hf-cache          # dedicated, token-free; mounted at /cache/huggingface

# Public key of your CONTROL HOST (the host you run these scripts from), so
# 00-node-prep.sh can authorize passwordless SSH to the `nvidia` user. Export it
# in your shell before running 00-node-prep.sh, or paste it here:
#   export CONTROL_HOST_PUBKEY="$(cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub)"
# CONTROL_HOST_PUBKEY="ssh-ed25519 AAAA... you@your-host"

# =============================================================================
# 2. QSFP fabric — one 200GbE cable, two PCIe-"twin" links per port.
# =============================================================================
# Each DGX Spark QSFP port enumerates as TWO netdevs (a PCIe x4 "twin" pair),
# each ~100G. Using both twins gets the full ~200G. The twins MUST live on
# DIFFERENT subnets (same-subnet breaks routing). Defaults below are arbitrary
# RFC1918 /24s — fine as-is unless they clash with your LAN.
QSFP_IF=enp1s0f1np1                 # rail 1 (primary; carries bootstrap/control + master-addr)
QSFP_IF2=enP2p1s0f1np1              # rail 2 (PCIe twin of the same physical port)
HEAD_R1=192.168.177.10              # head, rail 1
WORKER_R1=192.168.177.11            # worker, rail 1
HEAD_R2=192.168.178.10              # head, rail 2
WORKER_R2=192.168.178.11            # worker, rail 2
MTU=9000                            # jumbo frames; must match on both nodes + both rails

# =============================================================================
# 3. NCCL / transports — bootstrap (sockets) and RDMA (IB verbs) are separate.
# =============================================================================
NCCL_SOCKET_IFNAME=enp1s0f1np1      # control-plane bootstrap rides rail 1
# Gloo carries vLLM's CPU-side process-group coordination. Pin it to the same
# stable QSFP rail instead of allowing hostname resolution to select a drifting
# LAN address. Leave this equal to NCCL_SOCKET_IFNAME unless you know why not.
GLOO_SOCKET_IFNAME=enp1s0f1np1
# RDMA data path. DEFAULT = both RoCE twins (full ~200G). 04-run-nccl-bench.sh
# A/B-tests this vs a single HCA; put the winning value here.
NCCL_IB_HCA=rocep1s0f1,roceP2p1s0f1
# RoCEv2 IPv4 GID index from `show_gids` (often 3). Leave EMPTY to let NCCL
# auto-select (the compose unsets an empty value). Pin it only if the bench
# shows auto-select picking the wrong GID.
NCCL_IB_GID_INDEX=
NCCL_CROSS_NIC=1
NCCL_IB_MERGE_NICS=1                # merge the two RoCE twins into one logical NIC for NCCL
NCCL_NET=IB
NCCL_IB_DISABLE=0

# =============================================================================
# 4. Serving image — the dspark-vllm-gx10 (vLLM 0.25.1) lane (see docs/03, docs/08).
# =============================================================================
# DEFAULT LANE (2026-07-15): a digest-pinned community GB10 port by `anemll` carrying
# vLLM 0.25.1, plus a thin upstream-fix layer (vLLM PR #47356). 05-build-image.sh pulls
# the base and builds the patched tag; 06 distributes the final image; both the base
# (unpatched rollback) and the patched tag stay present on both nodes.
# BASE_IMAGE_REF/DIGEST pin the pulled base by immutable digest so every rank runs
# bit-identical bytes. Replace with the digest YOU pull if it drifts
# (docker inspect --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}').
BASE_IMAGE_REF=ghcr.io/anemll/dspark-vllm-gx10
BASE_IMAGE_DIGEST=sha256:d0a0c050252dd0b64a3213c728d1c15db9eb37602593ba37534bc708dd223ae7
# Unpatched base (rollback target) — referenced by digest so it is bit-identical everywhere.
DSPARK_VLLM_BASE_IMAGE=ghcr.io/anemll/dspark-vllm-gx10@sha256:d0a0c050252dd0b64a3213c728d1c15db9eb37602593ba37534bc708dd223ae7
# Final patched serving image built by patches/vllm-pr47356-vgx10/.
DSPARK_VLLM_IMAGE=vllm-dspark-runtime:vgx10-cand1-pr47356

# ----- ROLLBACK: the prior 0.21.x lane (tonyd2wild recipe + FlashInfer #3615) -----
# The previously-shipped default. To roll back, comment out the four lines above,
# uncomment this block, then rebuild with bringup/05-build-image.prior-0.21.sh and
# re-render both nodes. See docs/08 (Prior production profile) for the full rationale.
# DSPARK_VLLM_BASE_IMAGE=vllm-dspark-runtime:dspark-nvfp4-stage-c
# DSPARK_VLLM_IMAGE=vllm-dspark-runtime:dspark-nvfp4-stage-c-fi3615
# BASE_IMAGE_REF=ghcr.io/bjk110/vllm-spark:unholy-fusion-prod-ready
# BASE_IMAGE_DIGEST=sha256:d8492e7677cf1b9aaa3344e0e6865efc468454013eee5ebabac85be90af027be
# RECIPE_REPO=https://github.com/tonyd2wild/DeepSeek-v4-Flash-DSpark-1M-NVFP4-KV-2x-DGX-Spark
# RECIPE_SHA=ea8264e6b1215d51d5861481414e60e07f4c86da

# =============================================================================
# 5. Model / weights — public repo, no Hugging Face token needed anywhere.
# =============================================================================
DSPARK_MODEL=deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-DSpark
SERVED_MODEL_NAME=deepseek-v4-flash-dspark

# =============================================================================
# 6. API bind — loopback by default (no unauthenticated LAN exposure).
# =============================================================================
# The vLLM OpenAI API binds here. Keep 127.0.0.1 unless you front it with auth;
# the compose uses `--network host`, so a 0.0.0.0 bind would expose an
# unauthenticated API on your LAN. See docs/05 (listener audit).
VLLM_HOST=127.0.0.1
API_PORT=8000

# =============================================================================
# 7. Serve profile — the "sweet spot" for a DEDICATED 2x GB10 pair.
# =============================================================================
# 1,048,576 is the model's true YaRN ceiling (65536 x 16). Higher boots but
# extrapolates past calibration (experimental). First rung of the OOM ladder.
MAX_MODEL_LEN=1048576
MAX_NUM_SEQS=12                     # concurrent streams; drop toward 4->1 under memory pressure
MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS=8192
# KV cache dtype. nvfp4_ds_mla is the DSpark MLA NVFP4 KV (the memory win). Drop to
# fp8 only when diagnosing garble (see docs/05 OOM ladder).
KV_CACHE_DTYPE=nvfp4_ds_mla
# CUDA graph capture size for the spec-decode decode path. Set it to keep decode graphed
# at higher concurrency — too small drops decode to eager. vLLM 0.25.1 changed its own
# internal default formula to MAX_NUM_SEQS*(MTP_NUM_TOKENS+1)*2 (capped at 512) — note the
# added *2 vs the prior 0.21.x formula. Carrying the old 48 (== 12*(3+1)) onto 0.25.1 ran
# the engine at half its intended capture ceiling; 96 (== 12*(3+1)*2) restores it and
# measured +KV-pool and a small C8 throughput gain. If MTP_NUM_TOKENS->5, raise to
# min(12*(5+1)*2, 512)=144. See docs/08.
MAX_CUDAGRAPH_CAPTURE_SIZE=96
# Prefill head-of-line (HoL) fix: caps each running long-prefill chunk so short
# requests interleave — short-request TTFT otherwise regresses badly under a long
# prefill. 0/unset DISABLES it. preflight.sh warns (never fails) if this comes
# unwired; the metrics-watch timer re-checks the RUNNING container. See docs/07.
LONG_PREFILL_TOKEN_THRESHOLD=4096
# 0.85 is the sweet spot for a DEDICATED pair (2.45M tokens measured via profiler sizing;
# 2,948,751 with the KV_CACHE_MEMORY_BYTES pin below). DROP to 0.80 if
# you co-locate other GPU processes (e.g. a vision sidecar) on the head — that trades
# KV pool for headroom (~2.0M). Never exceed ~0.86 on the shared 121 GiB unified pool.
# HARD CONSTRAINT (measured 2026-07-11): vLLM's startup preflight requires
# util × total_mem FREE at boot — with ~21 GiB of co-tenants resident, 0.85
# (103.4 GiB) can NEVER boot (ValueError in worker/utils.py request_memory, unit
# hits StartLimitBurst). Co-tenant ceiling ≈ 0.82, and that leaves ~0 headroom
# for the CUDA-graph pool (~0.9 GiB, allocated ABOVE util) — so 0.80 is the real
# co-located setting, not a conservative one. See docs/05 OOM ladder.
GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION=0.85
# Pin the KV pool in bytes instead of letting the boot-time profiler size it (PROMOTED
# 2026-07-17, docs/08 "Post-promotion updates"). When set, vLLM skips memory profiling and
# reserves exactly this many bytes for KV, IGNORING gpu_memory_utilization for KV sizing
# (util still bounds the total footprint). Why: the profiler's available-KV budget silently
# carries the sparse-MLA workspace (~2.8 GiB) + cudagraph capture (~0.9-1.7 GiB), so its pool
# came out smaller (2.28-2.38M tokens) AND varied boot-to-boot — the pin yields a LARGER pool
# (2,948,751 tokens = 120.5% of the prior 0.21.x lane's 2,446,083) with ZERO variance across
# boots. WARNING: there is NO safety clamp against actual free memory — a too-high pin OOMs a
# thin boot; 21316272128 (19.85 GiB) was chosen from clean-boot anchors. The compose emits
# --kv-cache-memory-bytes only when this is set, so revert = comment the line out (profiler
# sizing returns). Requires the PR #47356 layer already in the default image.
KV_CACHE_MEMORY_BYTES=21316272128
# DSpark speculative draft length. 3 + probabilistic draft is the garble fix —
# do NOT revert to greedy 5. See docs/03.
MTP_NUM_TOKENS=3
# Reasoning mode (see docs/06). on (DEFAULT — matches the proven production config the Performance
# numbers were measured at) = server-default thinking + the OFFICIAL V4-Flash reasoning sampling
# (temp/top_p 1.0, NOT R1's 0.6/0.95); read the chain-of-thought from message.reasoning (NOT
# reasoning_content on vLLM 0.21.x). off = non-think greedy (temp 0), byte-identical to the tuned
# recipe and the fastest first-token path.
# WARNING (on): reasoning is spent BEFORE the answer — give requests a generous max_tokens (>=1024)
# or content comes back empty (the max_tokens trap). Re-run eval-cluster.sh (garble gate) if you change this.
DSPARK_REASONING=on
# high (default) or max. max needs MAX_MODEL_LEN>=393216 (1M clears it); reserve max for low-concurrency.
DSPARK_REASONING_EFFORT=high

# --- vLLM 0.25.1 lane knobs (see docs/08) ---
# DeepSeek-V4's model classes lack the @support_torch_compile decorator vLLM 0.25's standard
# compilation pipeline expects, so 0.25.1 auto-enables a "breakable" CUDA-graph path for this
# model — =1 IS the supported route here (upstream, it is =1 that selects CompilationMode.NONE).
# KEEP =1. An early out-of-band =0 test looked like an acceptance/KV collapse, but a controlled
# in-band reproduction (2026-07-16) showed =0 boots and runs at baseline throughput, acceptance,
# and KV pool — neither a lever nor a trap. We keep the documented default. See docs/08.
VLLM_USE_BREAKABLE_CUDAGRAPH=1
# FlashInfer top-k/top-p sampler. KEEP =1: this lane's base carries FlashInfer 0.6.15-dev, which
# already includes the SM120/121 radix-top-k reset-race fix (FlashInfer PR #3615) that both fixes
# the earlier garble bug AND removes the stream-hang risk that newer generic GB10 advice worries
# about (vLLM #43885 / PR #44405) — same underlying fix, so no tradeoff exists here. See docs/08.
VLLM_USE_FLASHINFER_SAMPLER=1

# Advanced serve knobs (rarely changed; safe defaults). render-env.sh bakes these
# into .env.dspark, so they must stay defined even at their defaults.
VLLM_EXECUTE_MODEL_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=600            # per-step execute timeout; higher tolerates long 1M-ctx compiles
TILELANG_CACHE_DIR=/cache/huggingface/tilelang    # TileLang JIT cache, inside the mounted HF cache
# Triton kernel cache. MUST live on the persistent HF-cache bind. Under breakable-cudagraph
# (torch.compile disabled), vLLM's InductorAdaptor.initialize_cache() — which would otherwise
# redirect TRITON_CACHE_DIR under VLLM_CACHE_ROOT — never runs, so without this override Triton's
# cache falls through to the container-ephemeral /root/.triton/cache and is wiped on every
# container recreate (every watchdog self-heal / redeploy / reboot), cold-recompiling kernels and
# re-triggering the post-boot JIT-storm the warm-up was built to avoid. See docs/07, docs/08.
TRITON_CACHE_DIR=/cache/huggingface/triton
VLLM_DSPARK_CONFIDENCE_SCHEDULER=off              # DSpark confidence-based draft scheduler (experimental)
VLLM_DSPARK_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD=0.0              # only meaningful when the scheduler is on
SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT=30                               # seconds to finish in-flight requests on SIGTERM

# =============================================================================
# 8. Distributed rendezvous — vLLM native `mp` backend (no Ray).
# =============================================================================
MASTER_ADDR=192.168.177.10          # must equal HEAD_R1 (rendezvous rides the QSFP fabric)
MASTER_PORT=25000

# =============================================================================
# 9. Ops knobs.
# =============================================================================
WORKER_WAIT_SECS=600                # head preflight patience for the worker unit
BOOT_DEP_WAIT_SECS=300              # per boot dependency (QSFP IP, docker, peer SSH)
XID_NOTIFY_COOLDOWN_SEC=300         # per-code evidence/alert cooldown for the optional Xid monitor

# Optional memory-pool mutual exclusion: if this node also runs a single-node
# model service (e.g. a llama.cpp unit) that would fight the cluster for the
# shared unified-memory pool, set its systemd user unit name here. preflight.sh
# then refuses to start the head while that service is running, and
# cluster-enable.sh/disable.sh stop/restart it. Leave EMPTY to disable the check.
CONFLICTING_SERVICE=
